cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as image segmentation, object detection, and contour detection, which are typically categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also extensively uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for these tasks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel sparse boundary representation for hierarchical segmentation, which could potentially fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of CNNs for contour detection and region hierarchies also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
